class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] numbers, int target) {
        int left=0;
        int right=numbers.length-1;
        while(left<right){
            int sum=numbers[left]+numbers[right];
            if(sum==target){
                return new int[]{left+1,right+1};
            }
            if(sum<target) left++;
            else right--;
        }
        return new int[]{};
    }
}

Since the array is sorted, we place two pointers at the start (left) and end (right) of the array. At each step we check the sum of
numbers[left] and numbers[right]: if the sum equals the target we return the indices; if the sum is smaller we move left forward to increase
the sum, and if the sum is larger we move right backward to decrease the sum. By adjusting pointers this way, we efficiently find the pair in O(n) time.
